<p>We went from 125hp max in VT to 215 in Time. Plus a ton of extreme focii and all sorts of things that made POP virtually the last expansion that should have come out. After this, one cannot imagine to have an healthy balance between npcs and players. I still don't.</p>

<p>Omens adds quite a number of hunting grounds: big plus.<br />
It has only flagging concerned at the very end while supporting willing in into Anguish with a mob drop to complete the key: very big plus to me.</p>

<p>The 7 parts of the signet seems a good idea but a couple of signets are too time consuming for the process to be fun. I like the challenge of sewers but then the signet dropper should allways be up at instance start. Catacomb is a waste of time and terribly unfun.</p>

<p>Single group content is in general doable. MPG trials are too class restrictive in some cases. Adding variety is nice but with weaponry they went to far. The lockout timers on fail are just wrong. Ditto for raid content.</p>

<p>Lots of gearing options for single groups. Very big plus.</p>

