<p>Group and raiding content pretty polished. Some stuff in Anguish isn't or wasn't but the rest is pretty much finished. Difficulty on one group trials and raid trial a bit messy. Like boosting difficulty in both while guilds lost many if not most of their best geared and experienced players: VERY big minus. Big mistake to me.</p>

<p>Holy trinity isn't too tight. Mobs have some retarded snare proc that makes invis a must and an hassle. There's a limit to what people can stand for travelling. Omens is a tad beyond that limit. Remove that snare proc plskthx.</p>

<p>Overall they did much better than with GoD. </p>

<p>Some issues stand though. The use of charm looks like nil most of the time. The use of pacify greatly reduced. Most pulling is just tag and run. Very little skill involved. Selo speed mobs as the norm is a bit silly and annoying.<br />
Resist rates seem a bit too high according to some classes.<br />
Mob abilities a bit too much at times. Trash that rampages, flurries, etc with high attack. A bit extreme. </p>

<p>Last but not least: all spells being dropped is really exagerrated. Half of it should have been on vendors. They pushed it too far.</p>

<p>But globally they did quite a move. What is still lacking is some proactive communication on changes, be it on encounters, epics or classes. They could work it out smoother. And last, the whole 10 points per class doesn't seem to work too well. It should really change format.</p>
